explanation: The solution uses a breadth-first search (BFS) approach to explore all possible strings obtained by removing invalid parentheses. It maintains a queue of strings to process and a set to keep track of visited strings. The `isValid` function checks if a string is valid by tracking the balance of parentheses. The BFS explores all valid strings reachable from the input string by removing one invalid parenthesis at a time. The time complexity is exponential due to the branching factor of 2 at each step (removing or not removing a parenthesis). The space complexity is also exponential due to the queue and visited set potentially storing many strings.

